The Christian right or the religious right The Christian right, also known as the religious right, is a political and social movement that is characterized by its conservative beliefs and values rooted in Christianity. This group often advocates for traditional family values, pro-life policies, and a strict interpretation of religious teachings in public life. While some view the Christian right as a powerful force for moral values and social conservatism, others criticize it for being exclusionary, intolerant, and seeking to impose its beliefs on others through legislation. It is a complex and influential movement that continues to shape political discourse and policies in many countries around the world.
The Christian right draws additional support from individuals who prioritize traditional values, moral principles, and conservative beliefs in their approach to social and political issues.
